<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <% locals.mood = "Privacy Policy" %>
  <%- include('../partials/head') %>
</head>
<body>
  <!-- 
    This privacy policy is currently not released as its unfinished and describes some features that are not implemented yet.
  -->

  <main>
    <div class="view_header">
      <div><a href="/">mood tracker</a></div>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    </div>
    <p><b>WARNING: This privacy policy is currently not released as its unfinished and describes some features that are not implemented yet.</b></p>
    <p>Last Update: <b>2023-08-01</b></p>
    <p></p>
    <hr>
    <section id="what">
      <h2>What information do we collect and how is it used?</h2>
      <p>We collect and store the following data to provide access to the service and improve user experience:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your username: Used for basic access and identification purposes</li>
        <li>Hashed password (using bcrypt): To securely authorize you into your account </li>
        <li>Profile settings and privacy settings: To customize data collection and personalize the service</li>
        <li>Mood updates: Stored to provide analytics and insights into your mood, which you can view on your profile. The history is analyzed locally, but the data is stored on our side</li>
        <li>Some data may be accessible through our <a href="/docs">API</a> by others if they know your username.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The data is stored indefinitely by default, but you can limit the amount of days the mood history is stored up to, or disable the history entirely.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="managing">
      <h2>Managing your data</h2>
      <p>
        You can delete your account at any time, and we will immediately delete all associated data.
        Additionally, you can download a JSON file containing all the data we store about you in your profile settings.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section id="third_party">
      <h2>Third-Party Access</h2>
      <p>While some of your data such as current mood and the history may be accessed using our API, we will never sell or share your data to anyone else.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="cookies">
      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>Our website uses cookies to keep you signed in.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="changes">
      <h2>Changes to our Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes made to our Privacy Policy by specifying the date.</p>
      <p>Previous versions of this privacy policy can be accessed by checking the commit history on our <a href="https://github.com/zptr1/mood-tracker">GitHub repository</a>.</p>
      <p>You are advised to review our Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Such changes to our Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted on this page.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
  <style>
    p, li { max-width: 700px; }
    p, section { margin-bottom: 20px; }
  </style>
</body>
</html>